# Design Rule

## Visual Design Elements

- Keep headings in elegant Playfair Display style with royal blue emphasis.
- Prefer clean white backgrounds, subtle secondary sections, and card-based layouts.
- Preserve a professional editorial aesthetic with generous but controlled spacing.

## Mobile Adaptation Standards (Solidified)

- Keep page structure consistent with web/desktop; mobile should be a denser presentation, not a different information architecture.
- Prefer scale-down and compact typography over removing important modules.
- Header on mobile must keep brand title readable in a single line when possible; avoid forced wrapping and crowded controls.
- Mobile nav should remain horizontally scrollable if needed instead of truncating core navigation items.

## Table and Data-Dense Content

- For key data tables, keep desktop-equivalent columns visible on mobile whenever possible.
- Do not hide critical columns solely for mobile breakpoints (`hidden sm/md/lg`) in core market/review tables.
- Use touch-friendly horizontal panning (`touch-action: pan-x`, momentum scrolling) for overflow areas.
- If width is insufficient, apply compact density/scale classes (like `mobile-fit-table`) before dropping data columns.

## Mobile K-Line/Chart UI

- Keep top controls in a single row on mobile (horizontal scroll allowed), with compact button sizes.
- Reduce mobile chart control visual weight (smaller paddings/fonts) to maximize chart viewport.
- Avoid overlapping legends and controls; hide non-essential legend text on mobile when controls already communicate state.
- Reserve sufficient top spacing for chart controls and keep axis labels compact on small screens.

## Internationalization

- This is a multilingual website.
- For all user-facing text, use i18n message keys and translation helpers; avoid hardcoded strings.